The Federal Government is conducting a five- day induction training for over 500 newly recruited officers, on grade level 07-10 in the Federal Civil Service. The Acting Head of the Civil Service of the Federation (HOCSF), Mrs Folasade Yemi-Esan, in Abuja, while declaring the event open, said the programme was part of Federal Government`s effort to drive the vision of building a modern public service. She said the flagship induction programme signifies the commitment of the Federal Government to drive the vision of building a modern public service that provides world class services for sustainable national development to a whole new level. “This of course, explains the rationale for a Pilot Phase which is to enable us assess the efficacy of the content and also receive feedback from you so as to ensure that the wider and subsequent induction programmes meet set objectives. So I hope you all appreciate the privilege of being first beneficiaries by participating in this phase of the induction. An induction programme is the most fundamental kind of training every aspiring officer in any corporate setting must be subjected to, she said. While calling on the inductees to use this opportunity given to them by the federal government to work hard as the initiative, she said, would maximize their output in the course of service to the nation, Yemi-Esan also charged them to go the extra mile as well as engage in self-development so as to acquire more skills that will aid in improving the productivity of the service. Earlier in her welcome address, Dr Magdalene Ajani, Permanent Secretary, Service Policies and Strategies, office of the HOCSF, explained that the importance of the induction programme was to introduce the rudiments of the service to the newly employed officers. She explained that the training was one of the eight priority areas in the 2017-2020 Federal Civil Service Strategy and Implementation Plan (FCSSIP) of the office of the HOCSF; “ The aim of FCSSIP, according to her, is to re-design and re-launch the 3 core Modules on SMAT-P, LEAD-P and induction with the aim of developing appropriate and sustainable capacity Development template for the civil service”, she said.